# CLIP ChangeLog for x11-drivers/xf86-video-intel

*xf86-video-intel-2.99.917_p20170313-r1 (08 Nov 2017)

  08 Nov 2017; Nicolas Godinho <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +xf86-video-intel-2.99.917_p20170313-r1.ebuild,  -xf86-video-intel-2.99.917_p20170313.ebuild,
  +files/xf86-video-intel-2.99.917_p20170313-clip-fix-display-port-output-enumeration-with-mst-hub.patch:

  Rbump to include the fix (by Philippe Tr√©buchet) of the bad display
  enumeration issue when connecting the card to a Display Port MST hub. This was
  causing an infinite loop of X11 RANDR events announcing new display
  overloading the X server.

